cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.IT, cs.SI, cs.DS

The paper discusses the training of over-parameterized models, specifically two-layer linear networks, which is a common topic in the machine learning community. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also discusses optimization algorithms and hyper-parameters, which falls under the sub-category cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). The use of time rescaling and the study of discrete gradient dynamics suggest that the paper may also belong to cs.IT (Information Theory) and cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Finally, the paper deals with regression, which is a topic in cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms).
